text:
Decent zichar food. Affordable in today's market. But the pork chop is quite dry, not the best.
Salted egg rice was decent too. But lesser sauce than I thought.

Nice simple tze char stall with friendly staff. Tried both the salted egg yolk chicken & fish on 2 separate occasions - both were good & very fragrant. Also can order ala carte veg / meat dishes ($6-8). Recently start serving spinach soup. Recommended.
